;; Generation scope, expressed per dimension as everything-minus-excludes.
;; Each dimension is EITHER an explicit name set (#{...}) OR
;; {:all true :exclude #{...}} = "every resolvable entry minus these excludes".
;;
;; :components — {:all true} covers every docgen entry exported by a wrapped
;;   @mantine/* package (core, notifications, ...; never @mantine/hooks), minus
;;   :exclude. That is the whole @mantine/core surface today.
;; :hooks — {:all true} covers EVERY export of the @mantine/hooks barrel: use* hooks
;;   AND the non-hook plain utilities (randomId, mergeRefs, clamp, the *Mask
;;   family, ...). hooks-ns-plan routes each: use* -> hook-docstring, else ->
;;   util-docstring (drift-guarded against codegen/input/util-docs.edn).
;;   `range` collides with clojure.core and is refer-clojure-excluded automatically.
;;   The lone exclude is normalizeRadialValue, the one barrel export with no
;;   upstream docs; any further undocumented export fails the build until it is
;;   documented or listed here. Companion hooks — use* exports documented on a
;;   sibling's docs page, so they carry no description in hook-docs.edn — are still
;;   generated; codegen/input/hook-docs-page.edn maps each to its shared docs page
;;   (useFullscreenDocument/Element -> use-fullscreen, useSessionStorage ->
;;   use-local-storage, useMousePosition -> use-mouse, etc.).
;; :supplement-only-packages — packages with NO docgen entries, so they never enter
;;   the component grouping and get no generated ns from docgen. Each named package
;;   gets a generated ns whose body is entirely its hoisted codegen/supplements/
;;   <suffix>.cljc (no components). @mantine/form is pure hooks + functions.
{:components {:all true :exclude #{}}
 :supplement-only-packages #{"@mantine/form"}
 :hooks {:all true :exclude #{"normalizeRadialValue"}}}
